{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4515"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4515"},"text":"§ 4515.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Personnel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4515/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to title III of the Federal Housing Finance Regulatory Reform Act of 2008, the Director may appoint and fix the compensation of such officers and employees of the Agency as the Director considers necessary to carry out the functions of the Director and the Agency. Officers and employees may be paid without regard to the provisions of chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of title 5 relating to classification and General Schedule pay rates.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4515/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Comparability of compensation with Federal banking agencies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In fixing and directing compensation under subsection (a), the Director shall consult with, and maintain comparability with compensation of officers and employees of the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency, the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, and the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4515/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Personnel of other Federal agencies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In carrying out the duties of the Agency, the Director may use information, services, staff, and facilities of any executive agency, independent agency, or department on a reimbursable basis, with the consent of such agency or department.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s4515/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Outside experts and consultants","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any provision of law limiting pay or compensation, the Director may appoint and compensate such outside experts and consultants as the Director determines necessary to assist the work of the Agency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddd25aaf9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/550/tXIII/s1315"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–550, title XIII, § 1315","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3947"},"text":"106 Stat. 3947","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/dA/tI/s1161/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, div. A, title I, § 1161(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-07-30"},"text":"July 30, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/2778"},"text":"122 Stat. 2778","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/tIII/s365/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, title III, § 365(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1555"},"text":"124 Stat. 1555","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddd25aafa-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddd25aafb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddd25aafc-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Housing Finance Regulatory Reform Act of 2008, referred to in subsec. (a), is div. A of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-07-30"},"text":"July 30, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/2659"},"text":"122 Stat. 2659","children":[],"tail":". Title III of div. A of the "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289","children":[],"tail":" is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s4511"},"text":"section 4511 of this title","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289","children":[],"tail":" to the Code, see Short Title note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s4501"},"text":"section 4501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddd25aafd-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":" substituted “and the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.” for “the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, and the Office of Thrift Supervision.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1161/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1161(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “In General” for “Office personnel” in heading, “Subject to title III of the Federal Housing Finance Regulatory Reform Act of 2008, the” for “The”, and “the Agency” for “the Office” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1161/a/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1161(a)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Agency” for “the Office”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1161/a/1/D"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1161(a)(1)(D)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (e) as (d) and struck out former subsec. (d). Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “The Director shall reimburse the Department of Housing and Urban Development for reasonable costs incurred by the Department that are directly related to the operations of the Office.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1161/a/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1161(a)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", (D), substituted “the Agency” for “the Office” and redesignated subsec. (e) as (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/289/s1161/a/1/E"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–289, § 1161(a)(1)(E)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f). Text read as follows: “Not later than the expiration of the 180-day period beginning upon the appointment of the Director under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s4512"},"text":"section 4512 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Director shall submit to the Committee on Banking, Finance and Urban Affairs of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs of the Senate a report containing—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) a complete description of the equal opportunity, affirmative action, and minority business enterprise utilization programs of the Office; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) such recommendations for administrative and legislative action as the Director determines appropriate to carry out such programs.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddd25aafe-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"iddd25aaff-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2010 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":" effective on the transfer date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s351"},"text":"section 351 of Pub. L. 111–203","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s906"},"text":"section 906 of Title 2","children":[],"tail":", The Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
